The South African Weather Service says KwaZulu-Natal should expect 60% chances of thunderstorms later on Thursday afternoon.  Weather forecaster – Ayanda Nsele – says these weather patterns will persist till Friday night.   ”There are chances of showered and thunder showers … it will remain cloudy and cool. On Friday, it will clear and warm up along the eastern parts and there is a 30% chance of showers and thunder showers over the western part of the province,” explains Nsele. The video below is a full weather report for today:  